This paper involves the use of convolutional neural networks (CNNs) for autonomous driving, which falls under the computer vision (cs.CV) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-categories. The paper also discusses the testing of the CNN on a driving simulator, which involves robotics (cs.RO) and control systems (cs.SY). Additionally, the use of machine learning techniques for autonomous driving suggests that the paper may also fall under the machine learning (cs.LG) sub-category.
